# Git LFS tracking — large binary assets that exceed GitHub's 50 MB warning
# and/or 100 MB hard limit. All stored in LFS, pulled automatically on clone
# via `git lfs pull` (which `git clone` runs by default on LFS-enabled repos).
#
# Busytex TeX Live data packages (LZ4-compressed Emscripten file_packager
# output — preload texmf into the WASM engine's MEMFS at app start):
*.data filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Busytex WASM binary (pdftex 1.40.25 + xetex + luatex + bibtex8 + xdvipdfmx
# linked into one ~30 MB WebAssembly module):
*.wasm filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Line endings — force LF for all text so Windows contributors don't
# introduce CRLF pollution.
* text=auto eol=lf
